preambule.al:
Desiring to facilitate the
exchange of information with respect to
taxes;

li.al:
in
the case of Canada, the Minister of National Revenue or the
Minister’s authorised representative;

in the case of Aruba, the Minister in charge of
Finance or an authorised representative of the
Minister;

the
land territory, air space, internal waters and territorial sea of
Canada;

the continental shelf of Canada, as determined
by its domestic law, in accordance with Part VI of
UNCLOS;

the term “person” includes an
individual, a company, a trust, a partnership and any other body of
persons;

the term
“company” means any body corporate or any entity that is
treated as a body corporate for tax purposes;

the term “recognised
stock exchange” means any stock exchange agreed upon by the
competent authorities of the Contracting Parties;

the
term “applicant Party” means the Contracting Party
requesting information;

the term
“requested Party” means the Contracting Party requested
to provide information;

the
identity of the person under examination or
investigation;

to the extent known, the name and address of any
person believed to be in possession of the requested
information;
